#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.80"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.80:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:0.2"
msgid "8. Ānandavagga "
msgstr "8. Ānanda "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.80:0.3"
msgid "80. Cūḷanikāsutta "
msgstr "80. Lesser "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.227, sc1
msgctxt "an3.80:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:1.2"
msgid "“sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

#. VAR: sahassilokadhātuṃ → sahassīlokadhātuṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.80:1.3"
msgid "‘bhagavato, ānanda, sikhissa abhibhū nāma sāvako brahmaloke ṭhito sahassilokadhātuṃ sarena viññāpesī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Ānanda, the Buddha Sikhi had a disciple called Abhibhū. Standing in the Brahmā realm, he could make his voice heard throughout the galaxy.’ "

msgctxt "an3.80:1.4"
msgid "Bhagavā pana, bhante, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kīvatakaṃ pahoti sarena viññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr "I wonder how far a Blessed One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha can make their voice heard?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:1.5"
msgid "“Sāvako so, ānanda, appameyyā tathāgatā”ti. "
msgstr "“He was a disciple, Ānanda. Realized Ones are immeasurable.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.80:2.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a second time … "

msgctxt "an3.80:2.2"
msgid "“sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.80:2.3"
msgid "‘bhagavato, ānanda, sikhissa abhibhū nāma sāvako brahmaloke ṭhito sahassilokadhātuṃ sarena viññāpesī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.80:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā pana, bhante, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kīvatakaṃ pahoti sarena viññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.80:2.5"
msgid "“Sāvako so, ānanda, appameyyā tathāgatā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.80:3.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a third time, Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "an3.80:3.2"
msgid "“sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.80:3.3"
msgid "‘bhagavato, ānanda, sikhissa abhibhū nāma sāvako brahmaloke ṭhito sahassilokadhātuṃ sarena viññāpesī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.80:3.4"
msgid "Bhagavā pana, bhante, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kīvatakaṃ pahoti sarena viññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr "“… I wonder how far a Blessed One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha can make their voice heard?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:3.5"
msgid "“Sutā te, ānanda, sahassī cūḷanikā lokadhātū”ti? "
msgstr "“Ānanda, have you heard of a thousandfold lesser world system, a galaxy?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:3.6"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo, "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "an3.80:3.7"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavā bhāseyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti. "
msgstr "Let the Buddha speak. The mendicants will listen and remember it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:3.8"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, suṇāhi sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:3.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. "

msgctxt "an3.80:3.10"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-the-travels-of-the-gods-and-the-sun-and-moon/4086
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.228, sc4
#. VAR: candimasūriyā → candimasuriyā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.80:4.1"
msgid "“Yāvatā, ānanda, candimasūriyā pariharanti, disā bhanti virocanā, tāva sahassadhā loko. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, a galaxy extends a thousand times as far as the moon and sun revolve and the shining ones light up the quarters. "

#. VAR: loke sahassaṃ → tasmiṃ sahassaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.80:4.2"
msgid "Tasmiṃ sahassadhā loke sahassaṃ candānaṃ, sahassaṃ sūriyānaṃ, sahassaṃ sinerupabbatarājānaṃ, sahassaṃ jambudīpānaṃ, sahassaṃ aparagoyānānaṃ, sahassaṃ uttarakurūnaṃ, sahassaṃ pubbavidehānaṃ, cattāri mahāsamuddasahassāni, cattāri mahārājasahassāni, sahassaṃ cātumahārājikānaṃ, sahassaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ, sahassaṃ yāmānaṃ, sahassaṃ tusitānaṃ, sahassaṃ nimmānaratīnaṃ, sahassaṃ paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ, sahassaṃ brahmalokānaṃ—"
msgstr "In that galaxy there are a thousand moons, a thousand suns, a thousand Sinerus king of mountains, a thousand Indias, a thousand Western Continents, a thousand Northern Continents, a thousand Eastern Continents, four thousand oceans, four thousand Great Kings, a thousand realms of the Gods of the Four Great Kings, a thousand realms of the Gods of the Thirty-Three, of the Gods of Yama, of the Joyful Gods, of the Gods who Love to Create, of the Gods who Control the Creations of Others, and a thousand Brahmā realms. "

msgctxt "an3.80:4.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatānanda, sahassī cūḷanikā lokadhātu. "
msgstr "This is called a thousandfold lesser world system, a ‘galaxy’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.80:5.1"
msgid "Yāvatānanda, sahassī cūḷanikā lokadhātu tāva sahassadhā loko. "
msgstr "A world system that extends for a thousand galaxies "

msgctxt "an3.80:5.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccatānanda, dvisahassī majjhimikā lokadhātu. "
msgstr "is called a millionfold middling world system, a ‘galactic cluster’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.80:6.1"
msgid "Yāvatānanda, dvisahassī majjhimikā lokadhātu tāva sahassadhā loko. "
msgstr "A world system that extends for a thousand galactic clusters "

msgctxt "an3.80:6.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccatānanda, tisahassī mahāsahassī lokadhātu. "
msgstr "is called a billionfold great world system, a ‘galactic supercluster’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#. VAR: tisahassimahāsahassilokadhātuṃ → tisahassiṃ mahāsahassiṃ lokadhātuṃ (s1-3, km) | tisahassīmahāsahassī lokadhātuṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.80:7.1"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, tathāgato tisahassimahāsahassilokadhātuṃ sarena viññāpeyya, yāvatā pana ākaṅkheyyā”ti. "
msgstr "If he wished, Ānanda, a Realized One could make his voice heard throughout a galactic supercluster, or as far as he wants.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.80:8.1"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, bhagavā tisahassimahāsahassilokadhātuṃ sarena viññāpeyya, yāvatā pana ākaṅkheyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“But how would the Buddha make his voice heard so far?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:8.2"
msgid "“Idhānanda, tathāgato tisahassimahāsahassilokadhātuṃ obhāsena phareyya. "
msgstr "“First, Ānanda, a Realized One would fill the galactic supercluster with light. "

msgctxt "an3.80:8.3"
msgid "Yadā te sattā taṃ ālokaṃ sañjāneyyuṃ, atha tathāgato ghosaṃ kareyya saddamanussāveyya. "
msgstr "When sentient beings saw the light, the Realized One would project his call so that they’d hear the sound. "

msgctxt "an3.80:8.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, tathāgato tisahassimahāsahassilokadhātuṃ sarena viññāpeyya, yāvatā pana ākaṅkheyyā”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a Realized One could make his voice heard throughout a galactic supercluster, or as far as he wants.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ → bhagavantaṃ (sī ), syā1, syā2, kaṃ potthakesu natthi. aṭṭhakathāya
msgctxt "an3.80:9.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to Venerable Udāyī, "

msgctxt "an3.80:9.2"
msgid "“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "an3.80:9.3"
msgid "yassa me satthā evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo”ti. "
msgstr "to have a teacher with such power and might!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:9.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Udāyī said to Venerable Ānanda, "

msgctxt "an3.80:9.5"
msgid "“kiṃ tuyhettha, āvuso ānanda, yadi te satthā evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo”ti? "
msgstr "“What is it to you, Reverend Ānanda, if your teacher has such power and might?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.80:9.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the Buddha said to Venerable Udāyī, "

msgctxt "an3.80:9.7"
msgid "“mā hevaṃ, udāyi, mā hevaṃ, udāyi. "
msgstr "“Not so, Udāyī, not so! "

msgctxt "an3.80:9.8"
msgid "Sace, udāyi, ānando avītarāgo kālaṃ kareyya, tena cittappasādena sattakkhattuṃ devesu devarajjaṃ kāreyya, sattakkhattuṃ imasmiṃyeva jambudīpe mahārajjaṃ kāreyya. "
msgstr "If Ānanda were to die while still not free of greed, he would rule as king of the gods for seven lifetimes, and as king of all India for seven lifetimes, because of the confidence of his heart. "

msgctxt "an3.80:9.9"
msgid "Api ca, udāyi, ānando diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyissatī”ti. "
msgstr "However, Ānanda will be extinguished in the present life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.80:9.10"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.80:9.11"
msgid "Ānandavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.80:10.1"
msgid "Channo ājīvako sakko, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.80:10.2"
msgid "nigaṇṭho ca nivesako; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.80:10.3"
msgid "Duve bhavā sīlabbataṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.80:10.4"
msgid "gandhajātañca cūḷanīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
